1
00:00:17,309 --> 00:00:20,103
[Scraping]

2
00:00:51,218 --> 00:00:54,429
No, son... never.

3
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:56,849
The blood stays on the blade.

4
00:01:00,227 --> 00:01:02,187
One day you'll understand.

5
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:13,949
AMSTERDAM: Some of it
I half remember.

6
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:16,869
And the rest...

7
00:01:16,952 --> 00:01:19,872
the rest, I took from dreams.

8
00:01:23,417 --> 00:01:26,712
St. Michael, the Archangel,
defend us in battle.

9
00:01:26,795 --> 00:01:29,047
Be our protector...

10
00:01:29,131 --> 00:01:31,633
against the snares...

11
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:35,179
and the wickedness
of the devil.

12
00:01:35,304 --> 00:01:37,389
Now, son... who's that?

13
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:38,390
St. Michael.

14
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:39,433
Who is it?

15
00:01:39,558 --> 00:01:41,560
- St. Michael!
- And what did he do?

16
00:01:41,643 --> 00:01:44,354
He cast Satan out of Paradise.

17
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:46,690
Good boy.

18
00:01:46,815 --> 00:01:49,276
[Flute and drum music plays]

19
00:02:53,841 --> 00:02:56,134
[Man speaking Latin]

20
00:02:56,218 --> 00:02:59,721
May God put the steel of
the Holy Spirit in your spine

21
00:02:59,847 --> 00:03:02,850
and the love of the
Blessed Virgin in your heart.

22
00:03:02,975 --> 00:03:04,852
[Music continues]

23
00:03:28,792 --> 00:03:30,127
Hey, boyo.

24
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,420
Johnny.

25
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:33,755
What's the battle?

26
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:35,507
Natives against
the Dead Rabbits.

27
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:36,675
Which are you?

28
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:39,303
What do you think?
Dead Rabbits.

29
00:03:50,314 --> 00:03:52,024
Aaah!

30
00:03:52,149 --> 00:03:54,943
Aaah! Aaah!

31
00:03:57,863 --> 00:04:00,240
[Indistinct shouting]

32
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:21,762
Well, well, Monk...

33
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:23,639
Are you with us or not?

34
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:26,433
For the last time, Vallon, I'm
with you if the money is right.

35
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:30,354
I'll give you ten per notch.

36
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,689
Ten?

37
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:35,275
You have my word.

38
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,697
Ten per notch?

39
00:04:40,781 --> 00:04:43,283
Per <i>new</i> notch.

40
00:04:46,828 --> 00:04:48,413
Then I'm your man.

41
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,375
[Music stops]

42
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:46,972
[Footsteps approaching]

43
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:38,524
BILL: Is this it, Priest?

44
00:06:38,607 --> 00:06:40,192
The pope's new army?

45
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:43,904
A few crusty bitches
and a handful of ragtags?

46
00:06:44,029 --> 00:06:47,658
Now, Bill, you swore this was
a battle between warriors,

47
00:06:47,783 --> 00:06:49,868
not a bunch of Miss Nancys.

48
00:06:50,035 --> 00:06:52,412
So warriors is what I brought.

49
00:06:55,958 --> 00:06:57,626
The O'Connell Guards!

50
00:06:57,751 --> 00:06:59,044
The Plug Uglies!

51
00:06:59,127 --> 00:07:00,963
The Shirt Tails!

52
00:07:06,677 --> 00:07:08,095
The Chichesters!

53
00:07:08,178 --> 00:07:10,973
The Forty Thieves!

54
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:22,234
<i>Bene.</i>

55
00:07:27,406 --> 00:07:29,783
On my challenge...

56
00:07:29,908 --> 00:07:32,786
by the ancient laws
of combat...

57
00:07:32,911 --> 00:07:36,081
we have met
at this chosen ground

58
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,625
to settle, for good and all,

59
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:42,796
who holds sway
over the Five Points...

60
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:46,300
us Natives, born rightwise

61
00:07:46,425 --> 00:07:48,802
to this fine land...

62
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:51,889
or the foreign hordes
defiling it!

63
00:07:51,972 --> 00:07:55,976
ALL: Yeah!

64
00:07:56,143 --> 00:07:58,145
By the ancient laws of combat,

65
00:07:58,312 --> 00:08:01,273
I accept the challenge
of the so-called Natives.

66
00:08:01,398 --> 00:08:03,817
You plague our people
at every turn.

67
00:08:03,942 --> 00:08:07,154
But from this day out,
you shall plague us no more.

68
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:08,822
For let it be known
that the hand

69
00:08:08,947 --> 00:08:10,908
that tries to strike us
from this land

70
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:12,993
shall be swiftly cut down!

71
00:08:13,118 --> 00:08:15,037
ALL: Yeah!

72
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:18,749
Then may the Christian Lord
guide my hand

73
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:21,084
against your Roman popery!

74
00:08:21,168 --> 00:08:23,420
Prepare to receive
the true Lord!

75
00:08:23,504 --> 00:08:25,547
ALL: Yeah!

76
00:08:25,672 --> 00:08:27,925
[Drums beating loudly]

77
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:35,849
[Slow, dramatic music plays]

78
00:08:57,246 --> 00:08:58,539
Aaah!

79
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:13,720
Aaaaahhhh!

80
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:27,753
Priest!

81
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:33,091
[Gasps]

82
00:10:49,358 --> 00:10:51,109
[Bagpipe music plays]

83
00:10:59,743 --> 00:11:01,954
[Blows]

84
00:11:02,037 --> 00:11:03,872
[Blows]

85
00:11:09,837 --> 00:11:13,882
Aaaaahhhh!

86
00:11:16,969 --> 00:11:18,762
Look to me!

87
00:11:20,973 --> 00:11:22,891
Who is this under my knife?!

88
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:34,444
Father, get up! Get up!

89
00:11:34,528 --> 00:11:36,029
Where are you?

90
00:11:36,154 --> 00:11:37,698
Where are you?

91
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:41,076
Oh, my son...

92
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:42,995
[Coughs weakly]

93
00:11:44,162 --> 00:11:47,499
Don't never look away.

94
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:57,176
Soon be over, Priest.

95
00:11:59,678 --> 00:12:01,346
Finish it.

96
00:12:05,726 --> 00:12:07,436
- [Knife plunges]
- Ugh!

97
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:12,649
[Knife withdraws]

98
00:12:12,733 --> 00:12:14,026
[Crying]

99
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:22,367
You may need this
across the river.

100
00:12:31,627 --> 00:12:35,172
Ears and noses will be
the trophies of the day.

101
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,092
But no hand shall touch him!

102
00:12:41,803 --> 00:12:44,806
No hand shall touch him!

103
00:12:46,642 --> 00:12:50,062
He'll cross over whole...

104
00:12:50,145 --> 00:12:51,730
in honor.

105
00:12:51,855 --> 00:12:54,650
Not before I get what's owed.

106
00:13:01,490 --> 00:13:02,241
No!

107
00:13:03,909 --> 00:13:05,494
BILL: It's fair...

108
00:13:05,619 --> 00:13:07,955
a touch indelicate, but fair.

109
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:14,795
My sympathies.

110
00:13:16,505 --> 00:13:18,340
MAN: What'll we do
with the boy?

111
00:13:18,465 --> 00:13:21,009
Look at me.

112
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:28,183
Give him to the law.

113
00:13:28,308 --> 00:13:30,269
See he gets a good education.

114
00:13:31,311 --> 00:13:34,106
Okay, boy,
say goodbye to your father.

115
00:13:37,651 --> 00:13:38,569
[Whooshes]

116
00:13:38,652 --> 00:13:40,195
- Hey.
- MAN: Hey!

117
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,738
[Indistinct shouting]

118
00:13:41,822 --> 00:13:42,573
Get him!

119
00:13:42,656 --> 00:13:44,157
Get him!

120
00:13:44,241 --> 00:13:45,868
Don't let him get away!

121
00:13:45,993 --> 00:13:48,036
Hurry! Come in here!

122
00:13:48,161 --> 00:13:49,621
Aaah!

123
00:13:49,705 --> 00:13:50,873
Aaah!

124
00:13:50,998 --> 00:13:53,041
- Aaah!
- He's going downstairs.

125
00:13:56,503 --> 00:13:59,089
[Panting]

126
00:14:01,008 --> 00:14:03,343
[Both panting]

127
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:07,681
[Continues panting]

128
00:14:09,558 --> 00:14:10,684
Come here, boy!

129
00:14:10,809 --> 00:14:12,269
You're going to
Hellgate, son!

130
00:14:12,394 --> 00:14:13,812
There he is.
Let's get him.

131
00:14:13,896 --> 00:14:16,815
BILL: Priest Vallon died
a noble death.

132
00:14:16,899 --> 00:14:21,695
But his Dead Rabbits is done
and outlawed!

133
00:14:24,072 --> 00:14:28,035
Let no one even speak their name
from this time on!

134
00:15:13,914 --> 00:15:15,624
M INISTER: In this place,

135
00:15:15,749 --> 00:15:19,962
you have grown
from a boy into a man...

136
00:15:20,087 --> 00:15:22,464
put to death
the earthly things in you...

137
00:15:22,589 --> 00:15:24,800
immorality, impurity...

138
00:15:24,925 --> 00:15:27,803
passion, vengeance.

139
00:15:27,928 --> 00:15:31,139
The Lord has forgiven you.

140
00:15:31,265 --> 00:15:33,892
You also must forgive.

141
00:15:35,769 --> 00:15:38,272
You go forth
to a country torn apart

142
00:15:38,438 --> 00:15:40,357
by civil strife.

143
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,067
Thank you, Reverend.

144
00:15:45,612 --> 00:15:48,532
Lend your hand to the work
that yet remains,

145
00:15:48,615 --> 00:15:50,492
that this war may end,

146
00:15:50,617 --> 00:15:52,703
and the plague of slavery

147
00:15:52,786 --> 00:15:55,539
that brought this conflagration
down upon us

148
00:15:55,622 --> 00:15:57,916
vanish forever...

149
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,043
from the Earth.

150
00:16:00,127 --> 00:16:02,588
[Door closes]

151
00:16:02,671 --> 00:16:04,923
[Crow caws]

152
00:16:09,344 --> 00:16:12,472
[Drum beating loudly]

153
00:16:18,562 --> 00:16:22,274
[Up-tempo music plays]

154
00:16:22,399 --> 00:16:25,360
[Cheers and applause]

155
00:16:29,406 --> 00:16:32,284
AMSTERDAM: In the second year
of the great Civil War,

156
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:35,120
when the Irish Brigade
marched through the streets,

157
00:16:35,245 --> 00:16:38,457
New York was a city
full of tribes...

158
00:16:38,540 --> 00:16:40,125
war chiefs...

159
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:41,960
rich and poor.

160
00:16:42,085 --> 00:16:43,629
MAN: Down with Lincoln!

161
00:16:43,754 --> 00:16:46,006
MAN #2: Lincoln will make
all white men slaves!

162
00:16:46,173 --> 00:16:48,133
AMSTERDAM:
It wasn't a city, really.

163
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:50,177
It was more a furnace

164
00:16:50,302 --> 00:16:53,847
where a city, someday,
might be forged.

165
00:16:53,972 --> 00:16:55,516
That's the spirit, boys.

166
00:16:55,641 --> 00:16:58,352
Go off and die
for your blackie friends.

167
00:16:58,477 --> 00:16:59,811
MAN: Down with
the abolitionists!

168
00:16:59,895 --> 00:17:01,563
We should have run
a better man against Lincoln

169
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:02,898
when we had the chance.

170
00:17:03,023 --> 00:17:05,067
MAN: New York should secede
from the Union!

171
00:17:05,192 --> 00:17:07,903
He trying to say we're
no different than niggers?!

172
00:17:08,028 --> 00:17:09,154
You ain't.

173
00:17:09,238 --> 00:17:11,823
- Good evening, brother.
- MAN: God save the Union!

174
00:17:11,907 --> 00:17:13,659
There's the Union.

175
00:17:13,742 --> 00:17:16,662
Go back to Africa, niggers!

176
00:17:16,745 --> 00:17:17,955
Go back to Africa!

177
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:20,082
- MAN: Leave him alone!
- We're free.

178
00:17:20,207 --> 00:17:21,208
AMSTERDAM:
The angriest talk

179
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:22,751
was of the
new Conscription Act...

180
00:17:22,876 --> 00:17:26,672
the first draft
in Union history.

181
00:17:26,797 --> 00:17:28,215
MAN: No nig noggery here!

182
00:17:28,298 --> 00:17:29,925
None!

183
00:17:31,969 --> 00:17:34,513
ALL: Yeah!

184
00:17:34,638 --> 00:17:38,183
BO Y: "New York Tribune"!
Buy your "Tribune" here!

185
00:17:38,308 --> 00:17:39,726
MAN: Join the Army, lads!

186
00:17:39,810 --> 00:17:42,020
Three square meals a day
and good pay!

187
00:17:42,145 --> 00:17:43,689
AMSTERDAM:
When the Irish came,

188
00:17:43,772 --> 00:17:45,566
the city was in a fever.

189
00:17:45,691 --> 00:17:47,609
Since the time
of the great famine,

190
00:17:47,734 --> 00:17:50,362
they'd come streaming
off the boats.

191
00:17:50,487 --> 00:17:52,531
And they got
a right warm welcome.

192
00:17:52,698 --> 00:17:55,075
MAN: Go back to Ireland,
you dumb Micks!

193
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,702
You remember that,
you bog-Irish gyps!

194
00:17:56,869 --> 00:17:58,078
Get back on the boat, Paddy!

195
00:17:58,203 --> 00:18:00,122
AMSTERDAM:
I only came two hours

196
00:18:00,247 --> 00:18:02,124
downriver from Hellgate.

197
00:18:02,249 --> 00:18:05,794
But they all took me
for an immigrant. Why not?

198
00:18:05,919 --> 00:18:08,130
There were a thousand different
accents in New York,

199
00:18:08,255 --> 00:18:09,381
and to the Natives, you see...

200
00:18:09,506 --> 00:18:11,133
[Chuckles]
It was all the same.

201
00:18:11,258 --> 00:18:13,969
[Translation from Gaelic]
Seven curses of God on you,
you bastard!

202
00:18:14,094 --> 00:18:15,804
Tammany's here to take
the chill off your soul

203
00:18:15,929 --> 00:18:17,472
and the weight off your heart.

204
00:18:17,598 --> 00:18:19,016
Welcome to America, son.

205
00:18:19,099 --> 00:18:21,310
Your long,
arduous journey is over.

206
00:18:21,435 --> 00:18:22,644
MAN: Go back
to your own country!

207
00:18:22,769 --> 00:18:23,854
Vote Tammany!

208
00:18:23,937 --> 00:18:25,981
MAN: America for Americans!

209
00:18:26,106 --> 00:18:28,192
[Up-tempo music plays,
fireworks exploding]

210
00:18:31,278 --> 00:18:34,198
AMSTERDAM: New York loved
William Tweed...

211
00:18:34,281 --> 00:18:35,866
and hated him.

212
00:18:35,949 --> 00:18:38,076
And those of us
trying to be thieves...

213
00:18:38,202 --> 00:18:40,287
well, we couldn't help
but admire him.

214
00:18:40,412 --> 00:18:43,207
Mr. Cutting, gentlemen,
thank you for coming.

215
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:45,375
- It's an honor.
- BILL: Mr. Tweed.

216
00:18:45,459 --> 00:18:46,460
[Birds chirping]

217
00:18:48,045 --> 00:18:49,171
Sir, please.

218
00:18:49,296 --> 00:18:50,422
Excuse me!

219
00:18:50,547 --> 00:18:52,216
I think
you're frightening them.

220
00:18:52,299 --> 00:18:53,550
So?

221
00:18:53,634 --> 00:18:55,719
Don't mind him.
He used to be an Irishman.

222
00:18:55,802 --> 00:18:56,887
[Laughter]

223
00:18:56,970 --> 00:18:58,222
[Mid-tempo music plays]

224
00:18:58,305 --> 00:19:00,098
AMSTERDAM:
Ah, the Five Points...

225
00:19:00,224 --> 00:19:01,934
Murderers' Alley...

226
00:19:02,059 --> 00:19:03,602
Brickbat Mansion...

227
00:19:03,727 --> 00:19:05,229
the Gates of Hell.

228
00:19:05,395 --> 00:19:08,524
REV. RALEIGH: It was here
in this vile place.

229
00:19:08,649 --> 00:19:11,443
Look upon the face
of this poor child.

230
00:19:11,527 --> 00:19:14,154
She lives in squalor

231
00:19:14,279 --> 00:19:18,784
in this godforsaken den
of vice and misery behind me.

232
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:21,620
Every year, the reformers came.

233
00:19:21,745 --> 00:19:24,665
Every year,
the Points got worse...

234
00:19:24,748 --> 00:19:26,250
as if it liked being dirty.

235
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:27,751
REV. RALEIGH:
...degraded men and women.

236
00:19:27,835 --> 00:19:29,962
MAN:
Where am I going to go?!

237
00:19:30,087 --> 00:19:32,005
MAN #2: Move! The Reverend
wants you out of here!

238
00:19:32,130 --> 00:19:34,132
You can't do this!

239
00:19:34,299 --> 00:19:35,551
Come on,
you filthy grubworm!

240
00:19:35,676 --> 00:19:37,344
REV. RALEIGH:
A glorious resurrection

241
00:19:37,469 --> 00:19:39,638
will spring
from the filthy depths...

242
00:19:39,721 --> 00:19:43,016
to which these miserable
creatures have fallen.

243
00:19:43,141 --> 00:19:46,019
In God, they will find
their true home.

244
00:19:46,144 --> 00:19:48,021
TWEED: You may
or may not know, Bill,

245
00:19:48,146 --> 00:19:50,023
that every day,
I go down to the waterfront

246
00:19:50,148 --> 00:19:52,693
with hot soup for the Irish
as they come ashore.

247
00:19:52,818 --> 00:19:55,112
It's part of building
a political base.

248
00:19:55,195 --> 00:19:57,823
I've noticed you there.
You may have noticed me.

249
00:19:57,948 --> 00:19:59,032
Indeed I have...

250
00:19:59,157 --> 00:20:01,535
throwing torrents of pavers
and withering abuse

251
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:03,537
on every single person
who steps off those boats.

252
00:20:03,662 --> 00:20:06,582
If only I had the guns,
I'd shoot every one of them

253
00:20:06,707 --> 00:20:09,293
before they set foot
on American soil.

254
00:20:35,903 --> 00:20:38,614
BILL: Mulberry Street...

255
00:20:38,739 --> 00:20:40,449
and Worth...

256
00:20:40,574 --> 00:20:43,619
- Cross and Orange...
- [Birds chirping]

257
00:20:43,744 --> 00:20:45,787
And Little Water.

258
00:20:45,913 --> 00:20:48,832
Each of the Five Points
is a finger.

259
00:20:48,916 --> 00:20:53,337
When I close my hand,
it becomes a fist.

260
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:55,839
And anytime that I wish,

261
00:20:55,923 --> 00:20:57,716
I can turn it against you.

262
00:20:57,799 --> 00:21:00,010
I understand, but we're talking
about different things.

263
00:21:00,093 --> 00:21:01,887
I'm talking
about civic duty...

264
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:03,722
responsibilities
we owe to the people...

265
00:21:03,805 --> 00:21:06,558
schools and hospitals,
sewers and utilities,

266
00:21:06,642 --> 00:21:09,061
street construction,
repairs, and sweeping,

267
00:21:09,144 --> 00:21:11,438
business licenses,
saloon licenses,

268
00:21:11,605 --> 00:21:12,856
carting licenses...

269
00:21:32,543 --> 00:21:35,087
St. Michael, the Archangel...

270
00:21:35,212 --> 00:21:37,256
defend us in battle.

271
00:21:37,381 --> 00:21:39,800
Be our protector against
the snares and the wickedness

272
00:21:39,925 --> 00:21:40,926
of the devil.

273
00:21:41,051 --> 00:21:44,012
TWEED: Streetcars, ferries,
rubbish disposal...

274
00:21:44,137 --> 00:21:46,765
There's a power of money
to be made in this city, Bill.

275
00:21:46,890 --> 00:21:47,933
With your help...

276
00:21:48,058 --> 00:21:51,436
the people must be made
to understand

277
00:21:51,603 --> 00:21:53,730
that all these things
are best kept within,

278
00:21:53,814 --> 00:21:55,816
what I like to call,
the Tammany family,

279
00:21:55,941 --> 00:21:57,985
which is why I'm talking
about an alliance

280
00:21:58,110 --> 00:21:59,987
between our two
great organizations.

281
00:22:00,112 --> 00:22:02,155
You're talking
about muscle work.

282
00:22:02,281 --> 00:22:03,240
That too.

283
00:22:03,323 --> 00:22:05,033
Muscle to match our spirit!

284
00:22:05,158 --> 00:22:06,910
You own the crushers.
Get them to do it.

285
00:22:06,994 --> 00:22:09,371
The police? Oh, no.
Jesus, no.

286
00:22:09,496 --> 00:22:12,875
The appearance of the law
must be upheld...

287
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,668
especially while
it's being broken.

288
00:22:14,793 --> 00:22:15,919
[Fireworks exploding]

289
00:22:26,847 --> 00:22:30,017
Give me the strength
for what I must do.

290
00:22:33,687 --> 00:22:35,439
JOHNNY: Who are you?

291
00:22:37,191 --> 00:22:38,609
- Ah!
- JI M MY: Hey!

292
00:22:38,692 --> 00:22:39,943
No.

293
00:22:40,027 --> 00:22:43,488
I said, "Who are you?"
What are you doing here?

294
00:22:50,871 --> 00:22:52,998
I just like it down here,
is all.

295
00:22:53,165 --> 00:22:54,458
[Chuckles]

296
00:22:54,583 --> 00:22:57,169
See what's
in his pockets, Jimmy.

297
00:22:57,294 --> 00:22:59,630
Now, look, boys,
I really don't want a fight.

298
00:22:59,713 --> 00:23:00,797
Don't want a fight?

299
00:23:00,881 --> 00:23:02,925
Don't worry, son,
ain't gonna be much a fight.

300
00:23:11,266 --> 00:23:12,726
Don't kill me.

301
00:23:12,851 --> 00:23:14,061
[Panting]

302
00:23:20,817 --> 00:23:22,361
Where'd you get that?

303
00:23:23,487 --> 00:23:25,322
I told you
I didn't want to fight!

304
00:23:25,447 --> 00:23:27,032
Why not?

305
00:23:27,199 --> 00:23:28,742
Look how good you done.

306
00:23:28,909 --> 00:23:30,744
- [Chuckles]
- [Laughs]

307
00:23:36,208 --> 00:23:38,085
You're the Priest's son,
aren't you?

308
00:23:38,210 --> 00:23:40,921
You, get away from me,
understand?!

309
00:23:41,046 --> 00:23:43,090
You don't remember me, do you?

310
00:23:43,215 --> 00:23:45,175
I's the one tried to help you.

311
00:23:47,636 --> 00:23:48,929
What?

312
00:23:49,054 --> 00:23:50,597
I's the one
tried to help you...

313
00:23:50,722 --> 00:23:52,349
when the Natives took you.

314
00:23:55,727 --> 00:23:57,896
Oh, that was you?

315
00:23:58,063 --> 00:23:59,106
Yeah.

316
00:23:59,273 --> 00:24:00,691
I thought you was killed.

317
00:24:00,816 --> 00:24:02,526
[Both chuckle]

318
00:24:03,819 --> 00:24:06,196
They just locked me up,
you know that?

319
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:08,031
This long?

320
00:24:08,115 --> 00:24:10,742
But I kept trying to escape,
you know.

321
00:24:10,826 --> 00:24:12,578
They add on time for that.

322
00:24:14,621 --> 00:24:17,374
So what are
you doing back here?

323
00:24:17,457 --> 00:24:19,877
I guess I missed the place.
[Chuckles]

324
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,461
[Horse neighs]

325
00:24:25,132 --> 00:24:26,717
[Laughs]

326
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:28,427
Bowery Boys. [Laughs]

327
00:24:28,552 --> 00:24:30,596
[Drum beating]

328
00:24:35,517 --> 00:24:37,060
MAN: That's enough now.

329
00:24:37,186 --> 00:24:38,896
[Man speaking Chinese]

330
00:24:40,189 --> 00:24:42,274
MAN: Hey! Get back here!

331
00:24:42,357 --> 00:24:43,775
The Five Points...

332
00:24:43,859 --> 00:24:45,110
Paradise Square...

333
00:24:45,194 --> 00:24:48,947
the streets here
are always lively of an evening.

334
00:24:49,031 --> 00:24:50,782
Who are the gangs around now?

335
00:24:50,866 --> 00:24:53,160
You got the Daybreak Boys
and the Swamp Angels.

336
00:24:53,285 --> 00:24:55,037
They work the river,
looting ships.

337
00:24:55,162 --> 00:24:57,122
The Frog Hollows
Shanghai Sailors

338
00:24:57,206 --> 00:24:58,790
down around the Bloody Angle.

339
00:24:58,874 --> 00:25:00,292
Shirt Tails was rough
for a while,

340
00:25:00,375 --> 00:25:02,461
but they've become a bunch
of jackrolling dandies,

341
00:25:02,586 --> 00:25:05,297
lolling around Murderers' Alley,
looking like Chinamen.

342
00:25:05,464 --> 00:25:07,758
Hell-Cat Maggie... she tried
to open her own grog shop,

343
00:25:07,883 --> 00:25:09,384
but she drunk up
all her own liquor

344
00:25:09,510 --> 00:25:10,969
and got throwed out
on the street.

345
00:25:11,094 --> 00:25:11,970
Beautiful.

346
00:25:12,095 --> 00:25:13,305
Now she's on the lay
for anything.

347
00:25:13,388 --> 00:25:14,765
There's the Plug Uglies.

348
00:25:14,848 --> 00:25:16,475
They're from somewhere
deep in the old country.

349
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:17,559
Got their own language.

350
00:25:17,684 --> 00:25:19,019
No one understands
what they're saying.

351
00:25:19,144 --> 00:25:20,312
They love to fight the cops.

352
00:25:20,395 --> 00:25:22,481
And the Night Walkers
of Ragpickers' Row...

353
00:25:22,606 --> 00:25:24,983
they work on their backs
and kill with their hands.

354
00:25:25,067 --> 00:25:27,861
They're so scurvy, only the
Plug Uglies will talk to them.

355
00:25:27,986 --> 00:25:29,530
But who knows
what they're saying?

356
00:25:29,655 --> 00:25:32,282
The Slaughter Housers
and the Broadway Twisters...

357
00:25:32,366 --> 00:25:34,201
they're a fine bunch
of bingo-boys.

358
00:25:34,326 --> 00:25:35,536
And the little
Forty Thieves...

359
00:25:35,661 --> 00:25:37,037
I used to run with them
for a while

360
00:25:37,162 --> 00:25:39,248
till they got took over
by Bendrick the Cockroach

361
00:25:39,373 --> 00:25:40,374
and his Red-Eyed Buggers.

362
00:25:40,541 --> 00:25:41,875
Bendrick carries a germ.

363
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:44,461
If you try to leave the gang,
he hacks up blood on you.

364
00:25:44,586 --> 00:25:46,004
MAN: The lime-juicers

365
00:25:46,088 --> 00:25:49,091
are nothing but a bunch
of rapacious grab-ups.

366
00:25:49,216 --> 00:25:51,593
The True Blue Americans
call themselves a gang,

367
00:25:51,718 --> 00:25:54,596
but all they do is stand around
on corners damning England.

368
00:25:54,721 --> 00:25:57,057
MAN: If you believe one word
that the British say,

369
00:25:57,182 --> 00:25:58,100
you're a fool.

370
00:25:58,225 --> 00:26:01,019
Do any of them got the sand
of the Dead Rabbits?

371
00:26:04,898 --> 00:26:07,150
You don't say that name.

372
00:26:07,234 --> 00:26:09,653
That name died with your...

373
00:26:09,736 --> 00:26:11,071
They've been outlawed.

374
00:26:12,781 --> 00:26:14,491
When I was in the blockhouse,
the Chinks told me

375
00:26:14,616 --> 00:26:17,661
that the Natives celebrate
their victory every year.

376
00:26:17,786 --> 00:26:19,204
Is that true?

377
00:26:19,288 --> 00:26:20,998
Aye, that they do.

378
00:26:21,081 --> 00:26:22,541
It's quite the affair.

379
00:26:22,624 --> 00:26:25,210
The Butcher himself's got to
invite you, or you don't go.

380
00:26:25,335 --> 00:26:27,296
[Indistinct conversations]

381
00:26:30,507 --> 00:26:33,260
Oh! Aah!

382
00:26:35,804 --> 00:26:37,890
Look where you're going,
Johnny.

383
00:26:41,476 --> 00:26:43,604
You look stunned
and poorly, sir.

384
00:26:48,692 --> 00:26:50,611
Quite a pair
of conversationists, aren't you?

385
00:26:50,736 --> 00:26:52,404
[Laughing]

386
00:26:52,529 --> 00:26:53,906
[Chuckles]

387
00:26:54,031 --> 00:26:55,407
Maybe not...

388
00:26:55,532 --> 00:26:57,242
but we're deep thinkers.

389
00:26:57,367 --> 00:27:00,621
[Laughing]

390
00:27:00,746 --> 00:27:01,955
Well...

391
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:06,126
Gentlemen, I leave you in the
grace and favor of the Lord.

392
00:27:06,251 --> 00:27:07,920
[Laughs]

393
00:27:14,051 --> 00:27:17,137
JOHNNY: Jenny... the finest
bludget in all the Points.

394
00:27:17,262 --> 00:27:19,723
She is
a prim-looking stargazer.

395
00:27:19,848 --> 00:27:21,517
Hmm.

396
00:27:21,642 --> 00:27:24,561
But I'd check my pockets
if I was you...

397
00:27:24,645 --> 00:27:27,523
'cause I do believe
she lifted your timepiece.

398
00:27:27,648 --> 00:27:30,067
[Harmonica music plays]

399
00:27:30,192 --> 00:27:31,818
MAN: Whoo!

400
00:27:31,944 --> 00:27:34,530
Well, I let her take it.

401
00:27:34,655 --> 00:27:36,740
I let her take things
all the time.

402
00:27:37,824 --> 00:27:39,701
Is that right?

403
00:27:39,826 --> 00:27:41,870
[Up-tempo music plays]

404
00:27:45,165 --> 00:27:47,626
AMSTERDAM: We always liked
a good fire in the Points.

405
00:27:47,709 --> 00:27:48,836
MAN: Fire!

406
00:27:48,961 --> 00:27:50,504
You could generally
pick up a little swag,

407
00:27:50,629 --> 00:27:53,257
and if the cops came along,
then you really got a show.

408
00:27:53,382 --> 00:27:54,383
TWEED: Vote Tammany!

409
00:27:54,508 --> 00:27:55,592
AMSTERDAM:
The Municipal Police

410
00:27:55,717 --> 00:27:57,761
fought the
Metropolitan Police.

411
00:27:57,886 --> 00:28:00,973
The Metropolitan Police...
they fought the street gangs.

412
00:28:01,056 --> 00:28:03,809
TWEED: Hurry up, men, before
the Black Joke get there!

413
00:28:03,892 --> 00:28:05,894
AMSTERDAM: There were
37 amateur fire brigades,

414
00:28:06,019 --> 00:28:07,396
and they all fought each other.

415
00:28:07,521 --> 00:28:10,315
WOMAN: The Black Joke
are on their way, Tweed!

416
00:28:10,399 --> 00:28:12,276
And they'll beat
the shite out of you.

417
00:28:12,359 --> 00:28:15,654
[Loud cheering]

418
00:28:15,737 --> 00:28:18,490
Okay, boys!

419
00:28:18,574 --> 00:28:21,159
Get the hose out!

420
00:28:21,243 --> 00:28:23,036
[Indistinct shouting]

421
00:28:26,957 --> 00:28:29,668
It's the Black Joke!

422
00:28:29,793 --> 00:28:32,171
Go get them, boys!

423
00:28:32,254 --> 00:28:35,215
MAN:
Give those Bowery Boys hell!

424
00:28:35,340 --> 00:28:37,009
Quick, before
there's nothing left.

425
00:28:37,134 --> 00:28:39,511
MAN: Go back to
the Bowery, you bums!

426
00:28:39,636 --> 00:28:42,014
MAN #2: Stop them! For God's
sake, they're taking everything!

427
00:28:42,139 --> 00:28:45,184
In your next time of trouble,
ma'am, call on Tammany first.

428
00:28:45,309 --> 00:28:47,186
But it's not too late!
You can still save my house!

429
00:28:47,269 --> 00:28:48,478
MAN: Whoo!

430
00:28:48,562 --> 00:28:50,230
Let's go.

431
00:28:51,481 --> 00:28:53,609
I thought you said
you was hungry!

432
00:28:57,988 --> 00:29:01,074
AMSTERDAM: Grab what you can!
Let's get out of here!

433
00:29:01,241 --> 00:29:04,953
MAN: May I point out that this
building is burning to ashes?

434
00:29:05,078 --> 00:29:06,914
And may I point out
that this area

435
00:29:07,039 --> 00:29:09,458
is the province of my own
Americus Fire Brigade

436
00:29:09,583 --> 00:29:11,919
and that you lot
belong only in the Bowery?

437
00:29:14,254 --> 00:29:16,298
May I point out that you're
outmanned, outmaneuvered...

438
00:29:16,423 --> 00:29:19,468
- [Music box plays]
...and, in a moment, outfought.

439
00:29:19,593 --> 00:29:20,802
Am I?

440
00:29:20,928 --> 00:29:23,555
[Loud cheering,
bell ringing]

441
00:29:27,351 --> 00:29:30,479
There's the Black Joke!
Let's take them on the cobbles!

442
00:29:30,604 --> 00:29:33,315
Go spill some claret, boys!

443
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:35,192
Go on, Shorty,
have a nice muss!

444
00:29:35,317 --> 00:29:37,277
MAN: Clear the way
for Bill the Butcher.

445
00:29:38,153 --> 00:29:40,364
Okay, boys, to work!

446
00:29:40,447 --> 00:29:42,366
What's the point?

447
00:29:42,449 --> 00:29:45,244
The fire's near burned
anything of value inside.

448
00:29:45,327 --> 00:29:48,705
Boys, forget that one!
Next building over!

449
00:29:48,789 --> 00:29:49,915
Mustn't let it spread!

450
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:51,166
Take what you want
from that one!

451
00:29:51,291 --> 00:29:53,210
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

452
00:29:53,293 --> 00:29:55,295
There's nothing wrong with
this one. This is my house!

453
00:29:57,631 --> 00:29:59,466
JOHNNY: Aah!

454
00:29:59,591 --> 00:30:00,551
- AMSTERDAM: Johnny!
- Help!

455
00:30:00,676 --> 00:30:02,427
Johnny!

456
00:30:02,553 --> 00:30:03,762
Help!

457
00:30:03,887 --> 00:30:06,265
Help!

458
00:30:06,431 --> 00:30:07,391
Help!

459
00:30:09,476 --> 00:30:10,894
Aah.

460
00:30:11,937 --> 00:30:12,938
Help!

461
00:30:17,693 --> 00:30:19,945
Come on!
Come on, Johnny! Get up!

462
00:30:20,070 --> 00:30:21,822
Leave that!

463
00:30:29,037 --> 00:30:31,039
TWEED: You two,
out of the way!

464
00:30:48,432 --> 00:30:50,642
His name's Amsterdam.

465
00:30:52,769 --> 00:30:53,979
How's the beak?

466
00:30:54,104 --> 00:30:56,023
Ain't so bad.

467
00:30:56,106 --> 00:30:58,317
You, you got anything,
you give it up,

468
00:30:58,442 --> 00:31:00,360
or you get out.

469
00:31:03,488 --> 00:31:05,282
[Clears throat]

470
00:31:07,826 --> 00:31:09,620
[Exhales sharply]

471
00:31:11,330 --> 00:31:12,372
Is that it?

472
00:31:13,540 --> 00:31:14,750
That's it.

473
00:31:17,211 --> 00:31:19,338
Right, here's the rake...
everything comes here.

474
00:31:19,463 --> 00:31:20,380
We fence it.

475
00:31:20,506 --> 00:31:22,174
Johnny takes our tribute
to the Natives,

476
00:31:22,257 --> 00:31:23,634
and we chop up
the winnings...

477
00:31:23,717 --> 00:31:27,596
each to his equal portion
amongst the gang.

478
00:31:27,721 --> 00:31:30,432
Does that meet
with your approval, Hellgate?

479
00:31:31,725 --> 00:31:32,935
My approval?

480
00:31:33,060 --> 00:31:36,438
What's the matter, Jack Sprat...
can't you think for yourself?

481
00:31:36,563 --> 00:31:38,106
[Chuckling]

482
00:31:38,232 --> 00:31:39,858
I'll slit your fucking throat!

483
00:31:39,942 --> 00:31:41,109
Hey, come on!

484
00:31:41,235 --> 00:31:42,528
[Door closes]

485
00:31:45,739 --> 00:31:49,535
You boys will settle with me
before settling with each other.

486
00:31:53,247 --> 00:31:56,208
I come for my due and proper.

487
00:31:57,417 --> 00:31:59,711
[Flute and drum music play]

488
00:32:12,641 --> 00:32:14,393
Oh...

489
00:32:14,476 --> 00:32:17,229
Well, this ain't a bad haul.

490
00:32:17,354 --> 00:32:19,231
You know when folks
start in to saying

491
00:32:19,356 --> 00:32:21,149
to where the country's
going to hell?

492
00:32:21,275 --> 00:32:22,317
I always tell them...

493
00:32:22,442 --> 00:32:24,027
"You just look
at all the hard work

494
00:32:24,152 --> 00:32:27,197
our fine young lads is doing
down in the Five Points."

495
00:32:27,322 --> 00:32:28,782
Oh, yeah...

496
00:32:28,949 --> 00:32:32,077
Now, this is just the thing
for Mrs. Mulraney.

497
00:32:32,202 --> 00:32:33,954
All right, there, Happy Jack,

498
00:32:34,079 --> 00:32:36,915
leave us with something to
quarter to Bill the Butcher, eh?

499
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:38,166
Would you?

500
00:32:42,963 --> 00:32:45,340
[Coughing]

501
00:32:47,050 --> 00:32:50,095
[Music box plays]

502
00:32:50,220 --> 00:32:51,763
Not my favorite tune.

503
00:32:51,889 --> 00:32:53,348
[Music stops]

504
00:33:00,355 --> 00:33:01,690
Thank you, boys.

505
00:33:02,983 --> 00:33:05,277
You keep out of trouble, now.

506
00:33:17,664 --> 00:33:19,666
[Speaking Chinese]

507
00:33:23,754 --> 00:33:25,756
AMSTERDAM: Every year,
the Natives celebrated

508
00:33:25,881 --> 00:33:28,300
the killing of my father
all over again...

509
00:33:29,927 --> 00:33:33,847
...at Sparrow's Chinese Pagoda
in Mott Street.

510
00:33:35,057 --> 00:33:37,976
The Chinks hated the Natives
worse than we did.

511
00:33:41,647 --> 00:33:46,109
The drum rolls, and the Butcher
drinks a glass of fire.

512
00:33:48,946 --> 00:33:51,615
When you kill a king...

513
00:33:51,698 --> 00:33:54,701
you don't stab him in the dark.

514
00:33:57,454 --> 00:34:02,334
You kill him where the
whole court can watch him die.

515
00:34:02,417 --> 00:34:04,837
[Indistinct conversations,
Irish music plays]

516
00:34:06,630 --> 00:34:08,841
Hey, got any timber?

517
00:34:08,966 --> 00:34:10,509
[Match strikes]

518
00:34:17,015 --> 00:34:18,684
[Conversations, music
continue]

519
00:34:18,809 --> 00:34:20,519
<i># As I walked down</i>
<i>To Chatham Street #</i>

520
00:34:20,644 --> 00:34:22,145
<i># A fair maid I did meet #</i>

521
00:34:22,229 --> 00:34:24,064
<i># She asked me</i>
<i>To see her home #</i>

522
00:34:24,189 --> 00:34:25,732
<i># She lived</i>
<i>In Bleecker Street #</i>

